Here is a different recruiter search query for the same tech domain:

• Senior DevOps Engineer with 7+ years of experience in MERN and GraphQL, knowledge of Docker, Kubernetes, and CI/CD pipelines;
• Strong understanding of cloud computing platforms (AWS or Azure) and ability to design scalable infrastructure solutions;
• Proficient in implementing monitoring and logging tools (ELK Stack, Prometheus, Grafana), ensuring system reliability and performance;
• Has experience with configuration management tools (Ansible, Terraform), automation scripts (Powershell, Python), and version control systems (Git, SVN);
• Proven track record of successful deployments, scalability, and high availability in cloud-centric environments;
• Excellent problem solving skills, able to debug complex infrastructure issues efficiently and effectively;
• Strong communication and teamwork skills, comfortable collaborating with cross-functional teams and stakeholders;

Here is a new query for the same tech domain:

* Data Engineer - Kafka Admin with 2-4 years experience, proficient in Kafka Streams, KSQL, and Confluent Control Center;
* Familiarity with data engineering pipelines using Scala or PySpark, dbt, and Airflow a plus;
* Excellent understanding of data quality, schema management, and data governance best practices;
* Prior experience working as part of a larger DevOps team, collaborating with Data Scientists and Engineers;
* Strong analytical skills to troubleshoot and resolve data-related issues; 
* Willingness to work on a rotating 12-hour night shift schedule (3pm-3am); 
* Location: San Francisco, CA or Phoenix, AZ; 
* Full-time opportunity available.

Need someone familiar w/ Next.js, React, & Tailwind, but this time for a Quality Assurance role:

* Frontend QA Engineer with 2+ yrs exp in automated testing using Jest, Mocha, or Cypress; strong understanding of unit testing, integration testing, and TDD/BDD concepts;
* Preferably some experience with CI/CD pipelines (e.g., CircleCI) and understanding of Codecov, Codequality, and other code metrics tools;
* Basic knowledge of frontend dev tools like Webpack, Babel, and ESLint a plus; experience w/ SCSS, CSS-in-JS a bonus;
* Strong analytical skills to review code quality & identify potential issues; excellent communication skills for working closely with devs, designers, and product teams;
* Ability to work independently, prioritize tasks effectively, and deliver high-quality results under tight deadlines;
* Must be available 2-3 days before starting date

DevOps Engineer needed for cloud-native DB development: 
• 3+ yrs' exp building & deploying scalable databases with Google Cloud SQL & Bigtable;
• Proficiency in Terraform for infrastructure management and AWS Lambda for serverless compute;
• Strong understanding of data modeling, API integrations, and collaborative DevOps processes;
• Comfortable working collaboratively as part of a remote team (PST-friendly) and flexible schedule;
• Bonus points if you've contributed to open-source projects or designed & implemented CI/CD pipelines;
• Full-time employment type preferred, contract opportunities considered for the right candidate; Ready to start ASAP!

